main event: An unidentified aerial visual sighting was reported in Antigo, Wisconsin in September 1952.
interesting points: A bright light about 60 feet in diameter was observed at an altitude of 1,000 feet,The light displayed a tumbling motion and emitted sparks,The duration of the sighting was estimated at 10-15 seconds,The object was consistent with a satellite but exhibited visual phenomena inconsistent with typical satellite behavior,No radar contact was made in the local area.
witness description: Caucasian, 35-year-old male from Wausau, Wisconsin, described as reliable
